01:16:34,399 --> 01:16:35,733
<b>greatest empire on earth."</b>

479
01:16:36,000 --> 01:16:37,833
<b>He was sentenced to three years in</b>

480
01:16:37,833 --> 01:16:40,133
<b>prison, then house arrest for life.</b>

481
01:16:40,699 --> 01:16:42,533
<b>He died in 1967,</b>

482
01:16:43,199 --> 01:16:44,166
<b>still under house arrest.</b>

483
01:16:44,533 --> 01:16:45,266
<b>The government didn't</b>

484
01:16:45,266 --> 01:16:46,666
<b>permit the public funeral.</b>

485
01:16:47,033 --> 01:16:48,966
<b>Iran's second democracy crushed.</b>

486
01:16:49,033 --> 01:16:51,333
<b>Now, if you've been following the</b>

487
01:16:51,333 --> 01:16:53,966
<b>evidence, you might think the America's</b>

488
01:16:53,966 --> 01:16:56,699
<b>fault narrative sounds pretty accurate.</b>

489
01:16:56,699 --> 01:16:58,466
<b>The CIA did overthrow a</b>

490
01:16:58,466 --> 01:16:59,433
<b>democratic government.</b>

491
01:16:59,933 --> 01:17:01,000
<b>The documents prove it.</b>

492
01:17:01,399 --> 01:17:02,966
<b>And the CIA admitted it.</b>

493
01:17:02,966 --> 01:17:04,933
<b>And the trauma this created is real.</b>

494
01:17:05,333 --> 01:17:08,399
<b>After 1953, Iranian politics became</b>

495
01:17:08,399 --> 01:17:10,600
<b>saturated with conspiracy thinking.</b>

496
01:17:11,133 --> 01:17:13,533
<b>Political polemics in Iran are replete</b>

497
01:17:13,533 --> 01:17:14,866
<b>with such terms as</b>

498
01:17:14,866 --> 01:17:16,966
<b>"tuteah," "jasous," "khianat."</b>

499
01:17:17,033 --> 01:17:19,666
<b>These words—plot, spy, treason—became central to</b>

500
01:17:19,666 --> 01:17:21,600
<b>how Iranians talked about politics.</b>

501
01:17:22,033 --> 01:17:22,866
<b>Every event got</b>

502
01:17:22,866 --> 01:17:24,466
<b>explained as foreign conspiracy.</b>

503
01:17:25,133 --> 01:17:26,133
<b>Every politician got</b>

504
01:17:26,133 --> 01:17:28,266
<b>suspected of being a foreign agent.</b>

505
01:17:28,800 --> 01:17:30,966
<b>This vocabulary treats Iranian politics</b>

506
01:17:30,966 --> 01:17:33,566
<b>as a puppet show, in which the real</b>

507
01:17:33,566 --> 01:17:35,533
<b>players are hidden hands.</b>

508
01:17:35,933 --> 01:17:38,066
<b>The belief that real decisions are made</b>

509
01:17:38,066 --> 01:17:39,066
<b>by foreign powers</b>

510
01:17:39,066 --> 01:17:40,733
<b>operating behind the scenes.</b>

511
01:17:41,199 --> 01:17:43,600
<b>That's the psychological legacy of 1953.</b>

512
01:17:44,033 --> 01:17:46,633
<b>Every regime since then has</b>

513
01:17:46,633 --> 01:17:48,166
<b>used the coup as justification.</b>

514
01:17:49,300 --> 01:17:50,666
<b>Every failure gets blamed</b>

515
01:17:50,666 --> 01:17:52,166
<b>on foreign conspiracies.</b>

516
01:17:52,933 --> 01:17:55,066
<b>So, where does this narrative go wrong?</b>

517
01:17:55,466 --> 01:17:57,199
<b>The coup was foreign planned,</b>

518
01:17:57,199 --> 01:17:58,966
<b>but it was Iranian executed.</b>

519
01:17:59,399 --> 01:18:02,166
<b>The events were steered, executed and</b>

520
01:18:02,166 --> 01:18:04,466
<b>operationalized by Iranians,</b>

521
01:18:05,000 --> 01:18:07,966
<b>who were directly and indirectly carrying</b>

522
01:18:07,966 --> 01:18:10,666
<b>out modified British US plans.</b>

523
01:18:11,000 --> 01:18:13,266
<b>Mosaddegh and his colleagues made a</b>

524
01:18:13,266 --> 01:18:14,533
<b>number of key strategic</b>

525
01:18:14,533 --> 01:18:15,966
<b>and tactical mistakes.</b>

526
01:18:16,533 --> 01:18:18,033
<b>Most importantly, they</b>

527
01:18:18,033 --> 01:18:19,600
<b>failed to create an organization,</b>

528
01:18:20,366 --> 01:18:21,833
<b>capable of mobilizing broad</b>

529
01:18:21,833 --> 01:18:23,433
<b>support for their movement.</b>

530
01:18:24,033 --> 01:18:25,166
<b>Foreign powers provided</b>

531
01:18:25,166 --> 01:18:26,466
<b>the plan and the money.</b>

532
01:18:27,033 --> 01:18:28,866
<b>Iranians provided the execution.</b>

533
01:18:29,333 --> 01:18:30,966
<b>And Mosaddegh made mistakes.</b>

534
01:18:31,466 --> 01:18:33,666
<b>He held referendums with separate ballot</b>

535
01:18:33,666 --> 01:18:35,166
<b>boxes for yes and no.</b>

536
01:18:35,466 --> 01:18:37,100
<b>Anyone could see how you voted.</b>

537
01:18:37,466 --> 01:18:38,500
<b>That's not real democracy.</b>

538
01:18:39,000 --> 01:18:40,266
<b>He took emergency powers</b>

539
01:18:40,266 --> 01:18:42,166
<b>that alienated former allies.</b>

540
01:18:42,866 --> 01:18:44,800
<b>He knew General Zahedi was plotting</b>

541
01:18:44,800 --> 01:18:47,066
<b>against him, but didn't act decisively.</b>

542
01:18:47,633 --> 01:18:48,966
<b>Does this justify the coup?</b>

543
01:18:49,766 --> 01:18:50,066
<b>No.</b>

544
01:18:50,533 --> 01:18:52,566
<b>But it explains why the coup succeeded.</b>

545
01:18:53,533 --> 01:18:54,533
<b>The CIA didn't</b>

546
01:18:54,533 --> 01:18:56,166
<b>overthrow a unified government.</b>

547
01:18:56,833 --> 01:18:57,933
<b>They exploited</b>

548
01:18:57,933 --> 01:18:59,666
<b>divisions that already existed.</b>

549
01:18:59,899 --> 01:19:01,066
<b>And the deeper problem is</b>

550
01:19:01,066 --> 01:19:03,066
<b>treating 1953 as the beginning.</b>

551
01:19:03,966 --> 01:19:05,266
<b>As we've seen, the</b>

552
01:19:05,266 --> 01:19:06,766
<b>pattern started in 1907.</b>

553
01:19:07,000 --> 01:19:09,533
<b>The 1953 coup wasn't a</b>

554
01:19:09,533 --> 01:19:10,866
<b>rupture in Iranian history.</b>

555
01:19:11,466 --> 01:19:12,766
<b>It was a repetition.</b>

556
01:19:13,533 --> 01:19:15,766
<b>The same pattern, different players.</b>

557
01:19:16,366 --> 01:19:18,733
<b>And treating 1953 as the original sin</b>

558
01:19:18,733 --> 01:19:20,266
<b>means waiting for America</b>

559
01:19:20,266 --> 01:19:21,866
<b>to fix what America broke.</b>

560
01:19:22,433 --> 01:19:24,033
<b>That's not a political program.</b>

561
01:19:24,300 --> 01:19:26,366
<b>That's learned helplessness.</b>

562
01:19:26,366 --> 01:19:27,333
<b>So this is what the</b>

563
01:19:27,333 --> 01:19:28,500
<b>evidence actually shows.</b>

564
01:19:28,833 --> 01:19:30,633
<b>The 1953 coup wasn't unique.</b>

565
01:19:31,100 --> 01:19:32,033
<b>It was the second verse</b>

566
01:19:32,033 --> 01:19:33,966
<b>of a song started in 1906.</b>

567
01:19:34,000 --> 01:19:36,833
<b>But what makes this a cycle, not just</b>

568
01:19:36,833 --> 01:19:38,800
<b>repetition, is what happened next.</b>

569
01:19:39,100 --> 01:19:40,066
<b>Each suppression</b>

570
01:19:40,066 --> 01:19:41,766
<b>radicalized the next generation.</b>

571
01:19:42,533 --> 01:19:44,733
<b>The trauma of 1953 shaped</b>

572
01:19:44,733 --> 01:19:46,266
<b>everything that came after.</b>

573
01:19:47,000 --> 01:19:50,166
<b>In 1979, Iranians rose up again.</b>

574
01:19:50,800 --> 01:19:51,766
<b>Millions in the street.</b>

575
01:19:52,466 --> 01:19:53,500
<b>They overthrew the Shah.</b>

576
01:19:54,000 --> 01:19:54,933
<b>They promised democracy.</b>

577
01:19:55,933 --> 01:19:57,500
<b>And then something strange happened.</b>

578
01:19:58,166 --> 01:19:59,933
<b>The revolution had promised freedom,</b>

579
01:20:00,333 --> 01:20:01,966
<b>created a new system of control.</b>

580
01:20:02,033 --> 01:20:04,133
<b>One that would prove even harder to</b>

581
01:20:04,133 --> 01:20:05,933
<b>challenge than the Shahs.</b>

582
01:20:06,133 --> 01:20:07,033
<b>How did that happen?</b>

583
01:20:07,500 --> 01:20:09,166
<b>And what does it mean that Iranians are</b>

584
01:20:09,166 --> 01:20:10,233
<b>still fighting the same</b>

585
01:20:10,233 --> 01:20:12,633
<b>fight 120 years later?</b>

586
01:20:13,433 --> 01:20:14,866
<b>That is part two.</b>

